# Chapter 5 - Exception Handling & File Handling

This chapter covers exception handling and file handling concepts in Java, focusing on error management and data storage.

## Topics Covered:
- Introduction to Exceptions
- try, catch, finally blocks
- throw and throws keywords
- Introduction to File Handling
- Reading and Writing Files
- File operations in Java

## Practice Programs:
- Handling arithmetic exceptions
- Using try-catch blocks
- Basic file read and write programs
- File-based data storage examples

## Purpose:
- Handle runtime errors effectively
- Prevent program crashes
- Understand file operations for data storage
- Build real-world programming skills

This chapter introduces important concepts for writing reliable and data-driven Java applications.
